cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper is about background subtraction, which is a common task in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes a matrix decomposition problem with regularization terms, which involves optimization techniques. This suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with video analysis, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia) and may involve security applications, which falls under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
